{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"3103c17a-6b35-4b87-8fb8-51f082b60d72","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Unsupported Target Frameworks in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — dropped (EOL). You'd need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net5.0`** — dropped (EOL). You'd need to move to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net462`** — still supported ✅\n\n**Other migration notes:**\n- MSTest v3 replaces the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages with a single **`MSTest`** meta-package.\n- `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` is still needed unless you adopt the new MSTest runner.\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to update your target frameworks to currently supported ones (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`) and consolidate the package references.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"302c2cac-a8f4-4b24-bf1e-3c746ce7eb7b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is multi-targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3. Let me think about the compatibility issues:\n\nMSTest v3 dropped support for older target frameworks. Specifically:\n- MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2+ (so net462 is the minimum, that should be fine)\n- MSTest v3 dropped support for .NET Core 3.1 and .NET 5.0 — it requires .NET 6.0+ for the .NET (Core) side\n\n\n- The migration also involves switching to a single `MSTest` meta-package instead of managing separate framework and adapter packages.\n\nSo the user will face compatibility issues with `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` since both are EOL and no longer supported by MSTest v3.","outputTokens":558,"requestId":"CFCC:1CA5E9:613C2F6:6D501AF:69EC26AD"},"id":"c0bef219-3f35-4e0e-b93d-a2c3ea89c2c0","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:28:10.332Z","parentId":"5808b131-882a-4a56-96ba-2405bdc34370"}
